Package: Ditwah
Title: Ditwah Storm Data and Tools for Storm Monitoring and Early Warning November 2025, Sri Lanka
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Thiyanga S.", "Talagala", , "ttalagala@sjp.ac.lk", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment=c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0656-9789"))
Description: 
 Ditwah provides a collection of tools for storm data management, 
 monitoring, and early warning applications in Sri Lanka. The package 
 supports the processing of station-level observations, including 
 rainfall, temperature, and humidity measurements, along with 
 time-stamped weather reports. It includes functions for detecting 
 extreme weather events, generating top and bottom summaries, 
 producing visualizations, and creating dashboard-ready outputs for 
 situational awareness. The Ditwah storm began impacting Sri Lanka on 
 25 November 2025.
